parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate or hatch can cause it to open unexpectedly while driving, leading to potential accidents or loss of cargo. In addition, the heavy weight of the liftgate can make it difficult for consumers to lift, posing a risk of injury.
symptoms: The rear liftgate or hatch opens unexpectedly while driving
the liftgate or hatch does not hold its position
the liftgate or hatch is too heavy to lift
the liftgate or hatch opens upon impact
the liftgate or hatch comes open when hitting a bump
the hydraulic system fails to hold the liftgate or hatch up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liftgate latch can cause the hatch to not open from the inside, making it difficult to access the cargo area, and potentially leading to stored items falling out while driving, which can cause accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The liftgate will not open from the inside
interior lights come on
the hatch rattles
difficulty in closing the hatch
jiggling sound when driving
stored items fall out when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door locking device can cause the door to not lock properly, potentially leading to accidents or theft.
symptoms: The locking device no longer activates from the driver's console.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed repair of the liftgate latch recall can cause continued inconvenience and potential safety risks to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The dealership does not have the necessary parts to perform the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of front suspension components, such as springs, control arms, and sway bar bushings, can lead to loss of vehicle control, reduced stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noises
vibrations
or clunking sounds from the front suspension
uneven tire wear
sagging or leaning of the vehicle
difficulty steering or maintaining directional control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motor mounts can cause the engine to shift excessively, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to other components.
symptoms: The engine shifts or moves excessively
loud noises or vibrations are present
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
difficulty steering or maintaining control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator fan can cause overheating, electrical system malfunctions, and even fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
the radiator fan is noisy or stops working
the electrical system malfunctions or shorts out
burning or smoke is present from the wiring or engine compartment.
